She could be a super model, she is super talented and super smart. She is my super woman and I am the most blessed man on the planet because of her.. Tonight Lisa takes the stage and receives her doctorate of education from @texastech University and I couldn’t be more proud. I have seen the behind the scenes work she has done to accomplish this and it is inspiring. She paid her way through all of college thanks to scholarships she earned through rodeo queening and she did all of it while working and riding and keeping me in line. She truly is a super woman. God had a special day when He created this one..

To say I was proud of Lisa Lucia would be an understatement. She and her little 🐥 Chick, set out with a goal in 2023, to qualify for the UPRA - United Professional Rodeo Association Finals and they did it !!! 

Experiencing the ups and downs of rodeoing first hand, I know what it takes to qualify to such an event, especially in the state of Texas where the talent pool runs deep. The miles, the money, the effort, riding and working your horse even when you don’t feel like it, going through the rigors of entering, competing, handling all of the set ups good or bad and pushing on even when it seems like everything is against you. You earned this. You trained an amazing and gritty horse, a horse that I had full intention of getting rid of, you both are perfect for each other.. Last year at this time you were preparing for the final leg of earning your doctorate from Texas Tech, ☑️ one year later you are an official qualifier to the UFR, ☑️ an association you were once a queen of, before you went on to win Miss Rodeo America. This is just the beginning and your talent and work ethic never cease to amaze me.
Congrats to all the qualifiers of this finals and the WNFR. Rodeoing is NOT for the faint of heart and seeing what they put themselves through to live their dream is both inspiring and why I do what I do. This is just the beginning. @llageschaar
